eq\sigma_2^2 \qquad TS: F^*= rac{s_1^2}{s_2^2} \] \[ RR: F^*\leq F_{\alpha/2;n_1-1,n_2-1} \cup F^*\geq F_{1-\alpha/2;n_1-1,n_2-1} \] \[ P=2\mbox{min}\left[P\left(F_{n-1,n-2}\leq F^*ight),P\left(F_{n-1,n-2}\geq F^*ight)ight] \] 1.4.2 Test for Equal Variances with Paired Samples A test for equal variances is given in (Snedecor and Cochran 1967), which we will describe here. The test is based on bivariate normal variables \(Y_1\) and \(Y_2\) with standard deviations \(\sigma_1\), and \(\sigma_2\), and correlation \(ho\). Define the difference \(D\) and the sum \(S\) as follow, along with their variances and covariance. \[D=Y_1-Y_2 \qquad S=Y_1+Y_2\] \[\sigma_D^2 = V\{Y_1-Y_2\}=V\{Y_1\}+V\{Y_2\}-2\mbox{COV}\{Y_1,Y_2\}= \sigma_1^2+\sigma_2^2-2ho_{12}\sigma_1\sigma_2\] \[\sigma_S^2 = V\{Y_1+Y_2\}=V\{Y_1\}+V\{Y_2\}+2\mbox{COV}\{Y_1,Y_2\}= \sigma_1^2+\sigma_2^2+2ho_{12}\sigma_1\sigma_2\] \[\mbox{COV}\{D,S\}=\mbox{COV}\{Y_1-Y_2,Y_1+Y_2\}=\] \[\mbox{COV}\{Y_1,Y_1\}+\mbox{COV}\{Y_1,Y_2\}-\mbox{COV}\{Y_2,Y_1\}- \mbox{COV}\{Y_2,Y_2\}=\sigma_1^2-\sigma_2^2\] The correlation of \(D\) and \(S\) is the covariance divided by the square root of the product of their variances. \[ho_{DS}=  rac{\mbox{COV}\{D,S\}}{ \sqrt{\left(\sigma_1^2+\sigma_2^2-2ho_{12}\sigma_1\sigma_2ight) \left(\sigma_1^2+\sigma_2^2+2ho_{12}\sigma_1\sigma_2ight)}}= \] \[  rac{\sigma_1^2-\sigma_2^2}{ \sqrt{\left(\sigma_1^2+\sigma_2^2ight)^2- 4ho_{12}^2\sigma_1^2\sigma_2^2}} \] Dividing the numerator and denominator by \(\sigma_2^2\) and defining \(\phi=\sigma_1^2/\sigma_2^2\), we obtain the following result for \(ho_{DS}\). \[ho_{DS}= rac{ rac{\sigma_1^2}{\sigma_2^2}-1}{ \sqrt{ rac{\left(\sigma_1^2+\sigma_2^2ight)^2}{\left(\sigma_2^2ight)^2}-4ho_{12}^2\left( rac{\sigma_1^2}{\sigma_2^2}ight) \left( rac{\sigma_2^2}{\sigma_2^2}ight)}}=  rac{\phi-1}{ \sqrt{(\phi+1)^2-4ho_{12}^2\phi} } \] Now, letting \(F=s_1^2/s_2^2\), the ratio of the sample variances, we compute the sample version of \(ho_{DS}\), 